title>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/22/01 9:40:19 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.toddalan.com/~berglund/ikp_hao.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Wizard Question</span><hr size=1> The biggest lesson I learned of my wizard, is don't listen to what anyone says.<br>
<br>
Play a wizard because you enjoy it.<br>
<br>
If you don't enjoy it, then find another class.<br>
<br>
<br>
I listened to long about Hell levels, and how difficult they are.... etc....<br>
<br>
Bull, they're longer, not harder. Hell I'm still 35 where all my friends are in there 50's now.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Do what you want, and the hell with what anyone says. <p>

-I began my journey with the intent to save the world. I ended it, realizing the world did not wish to be saved.

Wizard of the 35th Reckoning</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukordesh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kordesh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/22/01 9:50:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Can anyone explain this Al'kabor thing now? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sahhar>Sahhar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/22/01 10:14:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Wizard Question</span><hr size=1> Follow your heart or mind, but definetly DO NOT follow some of these boards. I am particularly referring of course to some of the rant threads. I can understand the aggravation oh too well of some of my fellow wizards who rant or post on &quot;out of mana&quot; when after reaching high levels they feel they cannot continue. That is fine &amp; I have no problem with these posts, they've earned the right to rant after all those levels. I do have a problem with those who post a rant &amp; blast the class upon their decision to give up after what they may consider uberly levels of mid 30's or so. Bah! I believe if you dont make it past at least 40 then fine, maybe a wizard is not right for you. Fair enough, it is not for everyone. But we, the wizards who are trying to grind into their 50's or the beginning wizards dont need to hear about these &quot;problems&quot; these people had with a wiz. Either we've been there &amp; had the fortitude to perservere, or we are just starting the class and get suddenly disheartened. I speak from experience as I started coming to this post long ago in search of wisdom &amp; help. I have found an abundance of both mind you. But I couldnt help but notice some of the rants that had me on the verge of giving up before I had even begun. Some of these threads were from people only in their mid 20's who just couldnt deal with the aggravation. I shudder to think I almost quit a great class IMO due to some advice from people who probably didnt know what they were doing anyways. My advice is that you're the only one who is going to be able to decide if this class is for you. I only suggest you not make your decision until you are perhaps 29 (long ways perhaps I know) but that particular level really made me see the light.Good luck! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utehutibloodstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tehuti Bloodstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/22/01 10:34:57 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.toddalan.com/~berglund/ikp_hao.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Wizard Question</span><hr size=1> Al'Kabor's spells are weak, mana-ineffiecient, and weak.<br>
<br>
I would say useless, but if you are very very creative for they are good for ultra-low greens.... maybe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uryll.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/22/01 11:00:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Wizard Question</span><hr size=1> I know I love my wizard, and all he can do.<br>
<br>
Do not read too much negativity and take it as the only thing we go through.<br>
<br>
Often enough I do not post about the wonderful day I had, or good fortunes. I share them with my RL friends, and forget to post them... <br>
<br>
When something gets too aggrovating, I sometimes post to vent.<br>
<br>
As I said, I love blasting, porting (just not ALL the time...but it is a great ability), and all the wizard offers.<br>
<br>
If you are still having fun, continue.. if it gets less fun... continue because it will get better... if you are having no fun, then change... no reason to do anything in a game that stops being fun.<br>
<br>
Cheers, and have good times and good travels...<br>
<br>
Ryll Umbra<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uethenilreborne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ethenil Reborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/23/01 12:10:23 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://homepage.ntlworld.com/coug4r/Ethsigsmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Wizard Question</span><hr size=1> /Agree Ryll<br>
<br>
Aye, search out any class board and you`l find them all filled with the negativity and complaints. It has long since become the nature of forums devoted to mmoprg`s that they become an area for airing grievence and venting steam. But there are many, many wonderful things about the wizard. Some great quests that send you to interesting places, the staff of the wheel is notably a nice and fairly unique early quest.<br>
<br>
And now with translocates we are finaly the real masters of arcane travel, elevating us above our druid brethren. Speaking of which, even on druid boards, you`l find lots of complaints. That should tell you something.<br>
<br>
But mostly these threads are arguing over details. In general wizards are a blast to play. <p><body bgcolor="Black">
